                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner with the counterpane; I asked her what she had got; she said only some rags; this was on the 14th of February, between six and seven o'clock in the evening; she had this counterpane under her arm; I went and told my mother, then I ran after her and took it away from her; my mother asked her what she was going to do with it; she said only to pawn it; she was in our house as servant.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18090215-108-person990">
